# Dropbox credentials for upload-dropbox.js (verify proof-video uploads).
# Copy this file to `.env` (same dir) and fill in the values. `.env` is gitignored.
#
# In CI the verify workflow passes DROPBOX_APP_KEY / DROPBOX_APP_SECRET /
# DROPBOX_REFRESH_TOKEN as env from GitHub Actions secrets, so no .env file is
# needed on the runner - env wins over .env. This file is for local runs and
# for the one-time `--auth` that mints the refresh token.
#
# ============================================================================
# One-time Dropbox app setup (~2 minutes, no app verification needed):
#
#   1. https://www.dropbox.com/developers/apps -> Create app
#   2. Choose:
#        API:     "Scoped access" (the only option)
#        Access:  "App folder"   <- recommended; sandboxes uploads under
#                                   /Apps/<App Name>/ in your Dropbox
#                 OR "Full Dropbox" to write anywhere
#   3. Name the app (anything, e.g. "tarmacview-verify-proofs").
#   4. Permissions tab -> check:
#        files.content.write   (upload files)
#        sharing.write         (create public links)
#      Click Submit.
#   5. Settings tab -> OAuth 2 -> Redirect URIs -> add:
#        http://localhost:49234
#      (the long-lived `--auth` flow uses this localhost callback)
#   6. Settings tab -> pick ONE auth path:
#
#      A) SHORT-LIVED (simplest, 4-hour token, NOT for CI):
#         "Generated access token" -> Generate -> paste below as
#         DROPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN. Re-generate when it expires.
#
#      B) LONG-LIVED (recommended, what CI uses, never re-auth):
#         Copy "App key"    -> DROPBOX_APP_KEY
#         Copy "App secret" -> DROPBOX_APP_SECRET
#         Then run:  node upload-dropbox.js --auth
#         A browser opens, you approve, DROPBOX_REFRESH_TOKEN is written
#         back here automatically.
# ============================================================================

DROPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN=
DROPBOX_APP_KEY=
DROPBOX_APP_SECRET=
DROPBOX_REFRESH_TOKEN=

# Where proof videos land inside your Dropbox.
# "App folder" access -> relative to /Apps/<App Name>/.  "Full Dropbox" -> absolute.
DROPBOX_UPLOAD_PATH=/verify-proofs
